{
  "texts": [
    "To collect tweets, the research used Infection Disease Ontology.",
    "The result after testing on Logistic Regression (LR), Naïve Bayes (NB), and Support vector machine (SVM) classifiers showed the best accuracy, with 84% for the LR model with a count vector.",
    "Alkhair et al. [63] performed another study to detect the content of fake news on YouTube.",
    "The study collected data related to rumors about three famous people in Arab countries (topic of the dataset), namely, Fifi Abdu, Adel Imam, and Abdelaziz Boutaflika.",
    "The study used features related to content: n-grams with TF-IDF.1 https://github.com/salmujaiwel www.ijacsa.thesai.org For the classification process, SVM, Multinomial Naïve Bayes (MNB), and Decision Tree (DT) were used."
  ]
}